  "_comment": "Source of truth for the Company Granary (goods sold FOR WHEAT, item-for-item). Edit this, then run scripts/generate_granary_tiers to rebuild the per-tier Easy NPC presets (granary_keeper_<tier>.npc.snbt) from the compiled granary_keeper preset. Wheat pricing is the BELL CURVE: baseWheat is the cost at PEAK instability (56, gym 7 — wheat at its strongest buys the most), and the generator bakes cost = baseWheat * (1 + (peakInstability - instability) * wheatSwingPerPoint) per tier, clamped to 1..64 (a single wheat stack). So goods cost MORE wheat early (stable money, wheat weak), the LEAST at the gym-7 peak, and more again after the HQ raid re-stabilises the CobbleDollar — wheat's purchasing power rises and falls with the plot. No restocks: maxUses is the total stock per tier (TradingData reset is effectively never). Item IDs validated against the Cobblemon 1.7.3 jar (no shiny_charm / bottle_cap / oval_charm on this version).",
